[1]
Date: Tue 12 May 2009 10:19:53 +0530 (IST)
From: Pradeep Nath <vspcadeep@yahoo.co.in>


re: ProMED-mail Anthrax, human, bovine - India: (AP) 20090511.1763
------------------------------------------------------------------
This is nothing new here. We face this almost every year; more during the
monsoon season when the cases are much higher. These always originate from
the Araku agency areas. The Government claims to have taken all precautions
but there is no let-up in the cases every year.

On our part we have and continue to request the Animal Husbandry to check
our cattle on a regular basis by their vets designated apart from our own
medical protocols every year. We follow strictly every year the entire
vaccinations and this for precaution as we are close to the border of
Orissa and hardly 70 km (43.5 mi) from Araku.

It is [known] that 80 per cent of the cattle sold in the market from these
areas are affected with contagious diseases like foot and mouth and anthrax
also. We have all the documentation based on our [checking] incoming animals.

--
