[Since yesterday's (11 May 2009) report the total number of human cases has
increased to "65", which is slightly more than 51 + 6 but still within the
bounds of normal newspaper reporting. It is always difficult to know
whether reporters separate the living from the dead when reporting "cases"
or give the current total, which can include the dead. Our thanks to
Merritt for forwarding these 2 accounts.

